rough fiction to the transformations of modernity. This book ultimately tells a different story about the novel's place in the constellation of Arab modernism, modeling an innovative method of open-ended inquiry based on the literary texts themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aArabic fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aArabic poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aDetective and mystery stories, Arabicy20th centuryxInfluence. 0aModernism (Literature)zArab countriesy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079135840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520390201?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520390201zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520390201/original  a978-3-11-079135-8 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA